{"atom_id":"ig34_p0329_a022","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":329,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSLNKID | Link ID | Char | | Identifier | An identifier used to link the response assessment to the related measurement record in another domain which was used to determine the response result. LNKID values group records within USUBJID. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0329_a023","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":329,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSLNKGRP | Link Group ID | Char | | Identifier | A grouping identifier used to link the response assessment to a group of measurement/assessment records which were used in the assessment of the response. LNKGRP values group records within USUBJID. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0329_a024","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":329,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSTESTCD | Assessment Short Name | Char | (ONCRTSCD) | Topic | Short name of the TEST in RSTEST. The value in RSTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). RSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: \"TRGRESP\", \"NTRGRESP\", \"OVRLRESP\", \"SYMPDTR\", \"CPS0102\". | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_HEADER","verbatim":"| Variable Name | Variable Label | Type | Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format1 | Role | CDISC Notes | Core |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| | | | | | There are separate codelists used for RSTESTCD where the choice depends on the value of RSCAT. Codelist \"ONCRTSCD\" is used for oncology response criteria (when RSCAT is a term in codelist \"ONCRSCAT\"). Examples: TRGRESP, \"NTRGRESP, \"OVRLRESP\". For Clinical Classifications (when RSCAT is a term in codelist \"CCCAT\"), QRS Naming Rules apply. These instruments have individual dedicated terminology codelists. | |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSTEST | Assessment Name | Char | (ONCRTS) | Synonym Qualifier | Verbatim name of the response assessment. The value in RSTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. There are separate codelists used for RSTEST where the choice depends on the value of RSCAT. Codelist \"ONCRTS\" is used for oncology response criteria (when RSCAT is a term in codelist \"ONCRSCAT\"). Examples: \"Target Response\", \"Non-target Response\", \"Overall Response\", \"Symptomatic Deterioration\". For Clinical Classifications (when RSCAT is a term in codelist \"CCCAT\"), QRS Naming Rules apply. These instruments have individual dedicated terminology codelists. | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSCAT | Category for Assessment | Char | (ONCRSCAT)(CCCAT) | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of related records across subjects. Examples: \"RECIST 1.1\", \"CHILD-PUGH CLASSIFICATION\". There are separate codelists used for RSCAT where the choice depends on whether the related records are about an oncology response criterion or another clinical classification. RSCAT is required for clinical classifications other than oncology response criteria. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSSCAT | Subcategory | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a further categorization of RSCAT values. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSORRES | Result or Finding in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Result of the response assessment as originally received, collected, or calculated. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSORRESU | Original Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Unit for RSORRES. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | (ONCRSR) | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for the response assessment, copied, or derived from RSORRES in a standard format or standard units. RSSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from --STRESC. --STRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. For Clinical Classifications, this may be a score. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized units used for RSSTRESC and RSSTRESN. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate the response assessment was not performed. Should be null if a result exists in RSORRES. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSREASND | Reason Not Done | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why a response assessment was not performed. Examples: \"All target tumors not evaluated\", \"Subject does not have non-target tumors\". Used in conjunction with RSSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSNAM | Vendor Name | Char | | Record Qualifier | The name or identifier of the vendor that performed the response assessment. This column can be left null when the investigator provides the complete set of data in the domain. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSMETHOD | Method of Test or Examination | Char | (QRSMTHOD) | Record Qualifier | Method of the test or examination. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a015","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSLOBXFL | Last Observation Before Exposure Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Operationally derived indicator used to identify the last non-missing value prior to RFXSTDTC. The value should be \"Y\" or null When a clinical classification is assessed at multiple times, including baseline, RSLOBXFL should be included in the dataset. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSBLFL | Baseline Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be \"Y\" or null. Note that --BLFL is retained for backward compatibility. The authoritative baseline for statistical analysis is in an ADaM dataset. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0330_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":330,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.3 Disease Response and Clin Classification (RS) — RS-Specification","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| RSDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a derived record (e.g., a record that represents the average of other records such as a computed baseline). Should be \"Y\" or null. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
